<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="crime-n">crime <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /kraɪm/    美 /kraɪm/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-u">1.★ <strong>[U] (泛指) 犯罪活动</strong></h4>
<p>illegal activities in general：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>an increase in <strong>violent crime</strong>
暴力犯罪活动的增加</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A lot of crime is against bicycles.
针对自行车的（盗窃）犯罪很多。</p></div>

<h4 id="2-c">2.★ <strong>[C] 罪；罪行</strong></h4>
<p>an illegal action (offence)：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>Crimes against</strong> the elderly are becoming more common.
危害老年人的犯罪活动越来越常见。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>不道德的行为；罪过</strong></h4>
<p>sth that is to blame：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>It’s a crime</strong> to waste food.
浪费食物是可耻的行为。</p></div></div>